    researchFindings: ["Comparative studies ranked GHRP-2 as the most potent GH releaser among the GHRP peptide family.","Japanese clinical trials supported regulatory approval as a diagnostic agent for GH deficiency assessment.","Research showed GHRP-2 enhanced slow-wave sleep duration and quality in human subjects.","Studies demonstrated less appetite stimulation compared to GHRP-6 at equipotent GH-releasing doses.","Preclinical research indicated potential cytoprotective effects in gastric mucosal cells."],
    risks: ["Moderate appetite stimulation, though less intense than GHRP-6.","Can elevate cortisol and prolactin levels, particularly at higher doses.","Water retention and potential effects on blood glucose metabolism.","Long-term safety of chronic use in adults has not been established in large trials.","Injection site reactions and transient flushing."],
